Enum Direction

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<Direction>
      core.Direction
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Direction>
public enum Direction
extends java.lang.Enum<Direction>

Describes an orientation for Elements in an Instance. A Direction can be between NORTHEAST and NORTH covering the full spectrum of angles. Every Direction has an identifier and angle.

Author:
Kristopher Ives
